#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:1
msgid "Supported Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:3
msgid ""
"This appendix presents the cuda-oxide feature matrix: every compiler "
"capability, runtime API, and hardware feature along with its current support "
"status. The data is drawn from the compiler/runtime sources and the test "
"suite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:7
msgid ""
"**Legend:** **Full** = tested and working, **Partial** = ships and works but "
"has a known gap (called out in the row description), **Planned** = on the "
"roadmap, **N/A** = not applicable or no identified need."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:13
msgid "Compiler: Memory Model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Feature"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Status"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "HMM / Unified Memory Management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "**Full**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"GPU directly reads/writes host memory without `cudaMemcpy`. Reference "
"captures in closures leverage HMM for host pointer access. Requires Turing+ "
"GPU, Linux 6.1.24+, CUDA 12.2+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Unified Struct ABI (no `#[repr(C)]`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Device struct layout matches host exactly. The compiler queries rustc's "
"actual layout and reproduces it with explicit padding in LLVM IR. Works with "
"`#[repr(Rust)]` default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Dynamic Layout Matching"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Compiler queries rustc's `fields_by_offset_order()` and byte offsets, builds "
"LLVM structs with correct field order and explicit padding bytes. "
"Independent of LLVM's datalayout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Pointer Distance (`offset_from`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`ptr_offset_from` / `ptr_offset_from_unsigned` intrinsics (and the "
"`offset_from`, `offset_from_unsigned`, `byte_offset_from`, "
"`byte_offset_from_unsigned` methods) lower to an address difference divided "
"by the rustc-reported pointee size, returning `isize` (signed) or `usize` "
"(unsigned). Errors on a zero-sized pointee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Volatile Load/Store"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`core::ptr::read_volatile` / `write_volatile` carry an explicit volatile bit "
"through MIR import, mem2reg (volatile accesses are never promoted), MIR-to-"
"LLVM lowering, and textual export (`load volatile` / `store volatile`). "
"Emits `ld.volatile` / `st.volatile` in PTX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Bulk Copy (`copy_nonoverlapping`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`core::ptr::copy_nonoverlapping` lowers to a `mir.memcpy` op and then `llvm."
"memcpy`, with the element count scaled to bytes for the pointee. The "
"intrinsic overload suffix is derived from the operand address spaces and "
"length width."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:24
msgid "Compiler: Type System"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Generics and Monomorphization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Generic kernels and device functions with trait bounds. Monomorphized "
"instances collected from rustc MIR. Const generics supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Enums (`Option<T>`, `Result<T,E>`, custom)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Full enum support including discriminant extraction and payload access. "
"Pattern matching on enums works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Struct Construction and Field Access"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Struct literals, field access, pass-by-value and return values. User-defined "
"structs supported without annotations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Array Types (`[T; N]`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Static construction, constant- and runtime-index access. Array value "
"constants (bare and nested) materialized. Mutable arrays auto-promoted to "
"memory-backed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`CuSimd<T, N>` SIMD Type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Generic SIMD register type with named accessors (`x`/`y`/`z`/`w`), runtime "
"and compile-time indexing, `to_array` conversion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "ABI Scalarization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Slices are scalarized at kernel boundaries (`&[T]` -> `(ptr, len)`, "
"reconstructed inside the function). Structs and closures pass by value as "
"one byval `.param`; field flattening still applies on internal device-to-"
"device calls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:35
msgid ""
"Array value constants are limited to primitive leaves (integers, `f16`, "
"`f32`, `f64`) and nested arrays of those. Arrays whose elements are structs "
"or other ADTs are not yet materialized as constants; they need layout-aware "
"field decoding rather than the primitive byte-slicing rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:40
msgid "Compiler: Closures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Move Closures (`FnOnce`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Closures that capture by value. The whole closure struct is pushed as one "
"byval kernel argument. `move |x| x * factor` pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Reference Closures (`Fn`/`FnMut`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Non-move closures that capture by reference. The closure struct (containing "
"host pointers) still travels as one byval argument; the GPU reads through "
"those pointers via HMM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Host-to-Device Closures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Closures defined on host passed to generic kernels. Polynomial evaluation "
"with captured coefficients tested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Device-Internal Closures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Closures created and used entirely on device, including closures passed to "
"device functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:49
msgid "Compiler: Control Flow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Match Expressions (integer switch)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Multi-way match on integers. Generates chain of conditional branches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Match on Enums"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Pattern matching on `Option<T>` and custom enums. Discriminant extraction + "
"payload access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "For Loops (range, iterator, enumerate)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Full iterator desugaring: range-based, `slice.iter()`, `enumerate()`, nested "
"loops, `break`, `continue`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "While Loops / If-Else"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Baseline control flow fully supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Break and Continue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`break` and `continue` in for/while loops, including early exit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Loop Unroll Annotations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "**Partial**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`#[unroll]` and `#[unroll(N)]` request unrolling of explicit counted `while` "
"loops. Nested loops and multiple `continue` paths work; full unrolling "
"preserves `break` paths and multiple exit targets, while partial unrolling "
"requires a positive-step `<`/`<=` loop with an invariant limit and only the "
"normal header exit. Requests are capped at 1,024 copies, 8,192 cloned "
"blocks, and 65,536 cloned operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:60
msgid "Compiler: Arithmetic and Casting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "64-bit Arithmetic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Full 64-bit integer arithmetic including shifts, bitwise ops, and descriptor "
"field packing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Type Casting (all kinds)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"IntToInt, IntToFloat, FloatToInt, FloatToFloat, Transmute (bitcast), "
"PtrToPtr, PtrToInt, IntToPtr, pointer coercions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Packed bf16x2 FMA"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`bf16x2::fma_bf16x2(a, b, c)` lowers to PTX `fma.rn.bf16x2`, two bf16 lanes "
"per `u32`. sm_80+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:68
msgid "Compiler: Interop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Bi-directional LTOIR Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Rust kernels call CUDA C++ device functions **and** C++ calls Rust device "
"functions. Via NVVM IR → libNVVM → LTOIR → nvJitLink."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Device FFI (`extern \"C\"`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`#[device] extern \"C\" { fn ... }` declarations for external LTOIR "
"functions. CUB/CCCL integration demonstrated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "MathDx FFI (cuFFTDx / cuBLASDx)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"cuFFTDx (8/16/32-point thread-level FFT), cuBLASDx (32x32x32 block-level "
"GEMM) via LTOIR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Tile interop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "**Experimental**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Inter-kernel interop works today: a [cutile-rs Tile kernel](https://github."
"com/NVlabs/cutile-rs) and a cuda-oxide SIMT PTX kernel can run in one host "
"process on the same CUDA stream over shared device tensors. Intra-kernel "
"Tile interop is work in progress and tracked in [#96](https://github.com/"
"NVlabs/cuda-oxide/issues/96)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Cross-Crate Kernels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Kernels and device functions defined in library crates with monomorphization "
"at the binary crate use site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:78
msgid "Compiler: Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`#[kernel]` Attribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Marks functions as GPU kernel entry points (`ptx_kernel` calling "
"convention). Multiple kernels per file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`#[device]` Helper Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Device-side helper functions callable from kernels. `#[inline(always)]` is "
"preserved as the LLVM `alwaysinline` attribute (emitted alongside the "
"convergent group and any `!dbg` scope), so `opt` honors the inline intent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Standalone `#[device]` Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Device functions compiled without any kernel present. Clean export names for "
"C++ consumption."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Multi-Kernel Modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Multiple `#[kernel]` functions in a single source file compile to a single "
"PTX module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:87
msgid "Compiler: Compilation Pipeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Unified Single-Source Compilation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Host and device code in the same file. Custom rustc codegen backend "
"intercepts codegen. No `#[cfg]` needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "PTX Output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Default output: Rust MIR → `dialect-mir` → `mem2reg` → annotated loop unroll "
"→ LLVM dialect → LLVM IR → `llc` → PTX. Targets sm_80 through sm_100a."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "NVVM IR Output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Selects LLVM 7 typed-pointer syntax for pre-Blackwell GPUs and opaque-"
"pointer syntax for Blackwell and newer GPUs. The generated module is "
"verified by libNVVM, and unsupported legacy operations produce a compile "
"error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "LTOIR Linking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Device-side LTO via libNVVM and nvJitLink."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Float Math Intrinsics (libdevice)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Rust `f32`/`f64` math methods (`sin`, `cos`, `exp`, `pow`, `sqrt`, ...) "
"lower to CUDA libdevice (`__nv_*`) on pre-Blackwell and Blackwell GPUs. cuda-"
"oxide selects the matching NVVM IR syntax automatically. On Blackwell, the "
"runtime can also JIT PTX produced from a standard pre-Blackwell target such "
"as `sm_86`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Pipeline Inspection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`cargo oxide pipeline <example>` shows imported and post-`mem2reg` MIR, LLVM "
"dialect, exported LLVM IR, and PTX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Compute Sanitizer Wrapper"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`cargo oxide sanitize <example>` builds the example and runs the host binary "
"under NVIDIA Compute Sanitizer (`memcheck`, `racecheck`, `initcheck`, or "
"`synccheck`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "cuda-gdb Source Debugging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`cargo oxide debug` builds device debug information on the PTX path and "
"launches `cuda-gdb`. Legacy NVVM IR does not yet support debug metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "cuda-gdb Local / Argument Inspection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`CUDA_OXIDE_DEBUG=full` is a `-G`-style build (optimization off, locals kept "
"in memory) so `info args`/`info locals` show real values for scalars, "
"pointers/references, and structs/tuples/arrays with their fields. Enums, ABI-"
"split bare slices, closures, and projections (`x.0`) are not yet described."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:101
msgid "Compiler: Inline PTX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`ptx_asm!` Macro"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"CUDA inline PTX with `%0` operands, `in`, zero or one `out`, up to 16 "
"inputs, CUDA register constraints `h`, `r`, `l`, `q`, `f`, and `d`, "
"immediate integer constraint `n`, `clobber(\"memory\")`, and "
"`options(register_only)` for pure register snippets. By default, snippets "
"are treated as side-effecting and stay inside their current control flow. "
"Use `options(register_only, may_diverge)` only for pure snippets that are "
"safe to move across divergent control flow; **never** use it for `.sync` "
"instructions or collectives. Multiple outputs, read-write operands, and the "
"`\"C\"` constraint are not implemented yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:109
msgid "Runtime Library: Safety"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`DisjointSlice<T, IndexSpace>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Bounds-checked parallel write output slice. `IndexSpace` rejects mismatched "
"layouts; uniqueness also requires matching prepared launch geometry (or a "
"raw unsafe proof)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`ThreadIndex<'kernel, IndexSpace>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Opaque, non-transferable witness. `index_1d` uniqueness requires inactive Y/"
"Z dimensions, proven by a `domain = 1` prepared launch or by the caller of a "
"raw unsafe launch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`PreparedLaunch<K>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Checked, reusable launch geometry branded for the exact kernel. Raw "
"`LaunchConfig` generated methods are unsafe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`ManagedBarrier` Typestate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Compile-time barrier lifecycle: `Uninit → Ready → Invalidated`. Invalid "
"transitions are compile errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:118
msgid "Runtime Library: Atomics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Device-Scope Atomics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`DeviceAtomic{U32,I32,U64,I64,F32,F64}` with `.gpu` scope. All 5 orderings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Block-Scope Atomics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`BlockAtomic{U32,I32,U64,I64,F32,F64}` with `.cta` scope."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "System-Scope Atomics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`SystemAtomic{U32,I32,U64,I64,F32,F64}` with `.sys` scope. For CPU-GPU "
"shared data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`core::sync::atomic` Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Standard library atomic types lowered to PTX `atom.sys` instructions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:127
msgid "Runtime Library: Shared Memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Static Shared Memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`SharedArray<T, N, ALIGN>` — compile-time sized, block-scoped. Optional "
"alignment up to 256B."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Dynamic Shared Memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`DynamicSharedArray<T, ALIGN>` — runtime-sized, set via `LaunchConfig::"
"shared_mem_bytes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Distributed Shared Memory (DSMEM)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Direct access to other blocks' shared memory within a cluster. "
"`map_shared_rank()` for address mapping. sm_90+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:135
msgid "Runtime Library: Thread and Synchronization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Thread/Block/Grid Intrinsics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`threadIdx`, `blockIdx`, `blockDim`, `gridDim`. Index witnesses are layout-"
"typed; their uniqueness also depends on matching launch dimensionality. "
"`index_2d_runtime(s)` adds a caller-proved stride. See [The Safety Model](../"
"gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Block Synchronization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`sync_threads()` — thread block barrier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Async Barriers (mbarrier)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Hardware async barriers for Hopper+: init, arrive, test_wait, try_wait, "
"inval."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Cluster Synchronization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`cluster_sync()` for all blocks in a cluster. sm_90+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Fence Operations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`fence_proxy_async_shared_cta()` for TMA visibility, `nanosleep(ns)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:145
msgid "Runtime Library: Warp"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Warp Shuffle Operations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`shuffle`, `shuffle_xor`, `shuffle_down`, `shuffle_up` for `i32` and `f32`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Warp Vote Operations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`all(pred)`, `any(pred)`, `ballot(pred)` → bitmask."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Lane/Warp ID"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`lane_id()` (0–31), `warp_id()`. Direct register reads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:153
msgid "Runtime Library: Cooperative Groups"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Typed Group Handles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`Grid`, `Cluster`, `ThreadBlock`, `WarpTile<N>` (N ∈ {1,2,4,8,16,32}), "
"`CoalescedThreads`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Group Universal API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`size()`, `thread_rank()`, `sync()` on every group handle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Warp Tile Partitioning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`ThreadBlock::tiled_partition::<N>()` carves a sub-warp `WarpTile<N>`. "
"`coalesced_threads()` materialises the active-lane group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Warp Collectives"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`ballot`, `all`, `any`, `shfl`, `shfl_xor`, `shfl_down`, `shfl_up` (`i32` "
"and `f32`); `match_any` / `match_all` (`i32` and `i64`); `active_mask`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Warp Reductions / Scans"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`warp_reduce`, `warp_scan` (inclusive). `Sum`/`Min`/`Max` for `u32`/`i32`/"
"`f32`; `BitAnd`/`BitOr`/`BitXor` for `u32`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Block Reductions / Scans"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`block_reduce`, `block_scan` (inclusive). Const-generic over `NUM_WARPS`; "
"same op/type matrix as warp variants; uses `__shared__` scratch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "Cooperative Kernel Launch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"`#[cooperative_launch]` on a `#[cuda_module]` kernel (or `unsafe "
"{ cuda_launch! { cooperative: true, ... } }`) enables `Grid::sync()` for "
"grid-wide barriers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:165
msgid "Runtime Library: Debug"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid "`gpu_printf!` Macro"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/supported-features.md:0
msgid ""
"Formatted GPU output with full format specifier support. Lowers to `vprintf`."
msgstr ""

